.TH "get_device_system_crosststamp" 9 "get_device_system_crosststamp" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
get_device_system_crosststamp \- Synchronously capture system/device timestamp
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" get_device_system_crosststamp
.BI "(int (*get_time_fn) (ktime_t *device_time, struct system_counterval_t *sys_counterval, void *ctx) "  ","
.BI "void *ctx "  ","
.BI "struct system_time_snapshot *history_begin "  ","
.BI "struct system_device_crosststamp *xtstamp "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "get_time_fn" 12
Callback to get simultaneous device time and
system counter from the device driver
.IP "ctx" 12
Context passed to \fBget_time_fn\fP
.IP "history_begin" 12
Historical reference point used to interpolate system
time when counter provided by the driver is before the current interval
.IP "xtstamp" 12
Receives simultaneously captured system and device time
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Reads a timestamp from a device and correlates it to system time
